<p><rs key="B_991170515093405501" type="letter">Epistolam tuam</rs><note type="editorial">Johann I Bernoulli hat diesen Brief offen an Michelotti gesandt, da Scheuchzer es Michelotti erlaubte, ihn zu lesen. (vgl. den Brief Johann I Bernoullis an Michelotti vom 27. März 1715)</note> sigillo signatam ad <choice><abbr>Clariss:<hi rend="sup">um</hi></abbr><expan>Clarissimum</expan></choice> <rs key="pers_DE-588-120379260" type="person">Scheuch<pc type="hyphenation">-</pc><lb break="no"/>zerum</rs> misi <rs key="place_GEO-3169070" type="place">Romam</rs>. Ipsum commendabo postquam
             <lb/>promotus fuerit D. <rs key="pers_DE-588-104265264" type="person">Morgagnus</rs> ad Anatomi<choice><orig><g ref="#ae">æ</g></orig><reg>ae</reg></choice> <rs type="organisation">Cathe<pc type="hyphenation">-</pc><lb break="no"/>dram</rs>. Dignum enim ut promoveatur ad <rs type="organisation">Cathe<pc type="hyphenation">-</pc><lb break="no"/>dram Theoric<choice><orig><g ref="#ae">æ</g></orig><reg>ae</reg></choice> Medicin<choice><orig><g ref="#ae">æ</g></orig><reg>ae</reg></choice></rs> in <rs type="organisation">Archilyceo Patavino</rs>, cen<pc type="hyphenation">-</pc><lb break="no"/>seo ipsum D. <rs key="pers_DE-588-120379260" type="person">Scheuchzerum</rs>.</p> <closer>Vale Vir Doctissime,
